# Zestra Capital Chart UI - Modular Source Code

Modular source code for the Zestra Capital Economic Analytics Chart UI. This structure breaks down the original 1075-line monolithic file into smaller, maintainable modules.

## Project Structure

```
chart-ui/
├── package.json          # NPM dependencies
├── webpack.config.js     # Build configuration  
├── src/
│   ├── index.js          # Entry point
│   ├── modules/
│   │   ├── Dashboard.js      # Core class (400 lines)
│   │   ├── DataFetcher.js    # API calls (150 lines)
│   │   ├── ChartRenderer.js  # Chart.js (250 lines)
│   │   ├── UIControls.js     # Events (200 lines)
│   │   ├── DashboardManager.js  # Manager (100 lines)
│   │   └── utils.js          # Utilities
│   └── styles/
│       └── dashboard.css     # All styles
└── dist/                 # Build output
    ├── zestra-dashboard.js
    └── zestra-dashboard.css
```

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install
npm install

# Build for production
npm run build

# Development with watch
npm run dev
```

## Using in WordPress Plugin

1. Build: `npm run build`
2. Copy `dist/zestra-dashboard.js` and `dist/zestra-dashboard.css` to plugin
3. No plugin code changes needed - API is identical

## Module Breakdown

- **Dashboard.js**: Main class, initialization, rendering
- **DataFetcher.js**: WordPress AJAX, search, data loading
- **ChartRenderer.js**: Chart.js integration, themes, timeframes
- **UIControls.js**: Event handlers, controls, sidebar
- **DashboardManager.js**: Global instance management
- **utils.js**: Helper functions

## Benefits

- Easier maintenance
- Files under 500 lines
- Better for AI modifications
- Easy to test
- 100% backward compatible

## Complete Usage Guide

See full documentation and file contents at: https://github.com/zestracapital/chart-ui/tree/main/src

For detailed module code, check individual files in the src/ directory.
